Stratified Univariate Negative Binomial Regression

Source: R/stratified_uni_nbin.R
stratified_uni_nbin.Rd

Performs univariate negative binomial regression for each exposure on a count outcome, stratified by a specified variable. Missing values in the stratifier are excluded.

Usage

stratified_uni_nbin(data, outcome, exposures, stratifier)

Arguments

data

A data frame containing the variables.

outcome

A character string specifying the name of the count outcome variable.

exposures

A character vector specifying the exposure variables.

stratifier

A character string specifying the stratifying variable.

Value

An object of class `stratified_uni_reg_nbin` with the following components:

$table

A `gtsummary::tbl_merge` object combining tables by stratum.

$models

A named list of fitted negative binomial models per stratum.

$model_summaries

A list of tidy summaries for each model.

$reg_check

(Optional) Diagnostics including dispersion checks.

Accessors

Use `object$table`, `object$models`, or `object$model_summaries` to extract components.

See also

[uni_reg_nbin()], [stratified_multi_reg()], [check_dispersion()]

Examples

if (requireNamespace("MASS", quietly = TRUE)) {
  data(Pima.tr, package = "MASS")
  Pima.tr$strata <- ifelse(Pima.tr$bmi > 30, "High", "Normal")
  strat_uni_nb <- stratified_uni_nbin(
    data = Pima.tr,
    outcome = "glu",
    exposures = c("age", "ped"),
    stratifier = "strata"
  )
  strat_uni_nb$table
}
